  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Our class took a taxicab in small groups to the old historic district downtown, since the school bus could not fit through the narrow streets.",
      "zh": "我們班分小組搭計程車到市區的老城歷史區，因為校車開不進那些狹窄的街道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The first stop was a small temple with a red roof, where an elderly man explained that people have prayed there for over a hundred years.",
      "zh": "第一站是一座紅色屋頂的小廟，一位年長的先生解釋人們在那裡祈禱已經超過一百年了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Right across the street stood an old church, and our teacher pointed out how the two very different buildings have shared the same block peacefully for decades.",
      "zh": "馬路對面就是一座舊教堂，我們老師指出這兩棟截然不同的建築物是怎麼在同一個街區和平共存了幾十年。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next, we visited a small museum built inside an old railroad station, with real train wheels displayed near the entrance.",
      "zh": "接著我們參觀了一間蓋在舊火車站裡的小博物館，入口附近展示著真正的火車輪子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The museum guide said many foreign visitors come specifically to see this old railway building, since nothing like it survived in other nearby cities.",
      "zh": "博物館導覽員說很多外國訪客特地來看這座舊鐵路建築，因為附近其他城市已經沒有類似的東西留下來了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice pointed out a foreigner taking photos of everything, and we guessed he might be a tourist visiting from abroad on a short trip.",
      "zh": "Bernice 指出一個什麼都在拍照的外國人，我們猜他可能是從國外來玩短期旅行的觀光客。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Near the old harbor, we saw a few small boats with white sails moving slowly across the calm water.",
      "zh": "在舊港口附近，我們看到幾艘掛著白色船帆的小船，緩緩地在平靜的水面上移動。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Someone joked that a boat ride might be faster than a flight to the next island, though nobody actually knew if that was true.",
      "zh": "有人開玩笑說搭船說不定比搭飛機到下一座島還快，雖然沒人真的知道這是不是事實。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, on a separate trip with his own school, said his group also visited a small temple, though his mostly remembered the free snacks afterward.",
      "zh": "另外和他自己班級出遊的 William 說他們那組也去了一座小廟，不過他大部分記得的是之後發的免費點心。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Before heading back, our teacher bought everyone a return ticket for the local train, saying riding it once is part of understanding this neighborhood's history.",
      "zh": "回程前，老師幫大家買了本地火車的回程票，說搭一次這班車也是理解這一帶歷史的一部分。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the train, Bernice waved goodbye out the window at absolutely no one in particular, just because she said it felt like the right thing to do.",
      "zh": "在火車上，Bernice 對著窗外根本沒有特定對象揮手道別，她說這樣做感覺就是對的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I wrote in my notebook that this was one field trip I would actually want to visit again someday, maybe even with my own family.",
      "zh": "我在筆記本裡寫下，這是一趟我以後真的還想再去一次的校外教學，說不定還想帶自己的家人一起去。"
    }
  ],
